# Domain Testing Rules

## After every domain change – run cucumber tests

```bash
npm run test:cucumber
```

Run this from `tms-api/` after any modification to a value object, entity, or aggregate.

## Spec placement

Spec files live **next to the implementation file**, not in a separate `tests/` folder.

```
src/cargo-plans/cargo-load-plans/
  cargo-load-plan.ts           ← implementation
  cargo-load-plan.feature      ← gherkin scenarios
  cargo-load-plan.steps.ts     ← step definitions

src/cargo-plans/pallets/
  pallet-spec.ts
  pallet-spec.feature
  pallet-spec.steps.ts
```

## Coverage requirement

Every domain class with behaviour must have a `.feature` + `.steps.ts` pair:

| Domain concept | Needs cucumber spec? |
|---|---|
| Value object with validation/logic | ✅ |
| Entity with state transitions | ✅ |
| Aggregate with invariants | ✅ |
| Pure data/DTO with no logic | ❌ |

## Scenario scope

Scenarios must cover:
- Happy path (valid state transitions)
- All domain invariants / guard conditions → expect the exact error message thrown
- Capacity / constraint boundaries
